text.section:
A person who leases vehicles to lessees may not:
Make any false, falsely disparaging, or misleading oral or written statement, visual description, or other representation of any kind that has the capacity, tendency, or effect of deceiving or misleading a consumer or lessee;
By any means advertise or offer to the public any motor vehicle without intent to lease it as advertised or offered;
Misrepresent a lease of a motor vehicle as a sale;
Fail to include any dealer processing or freight charges in determining the adjusted capitalized cost used to calculate the base lease payment shown in an advertisement for a leased vehicle; or
Advertise to the general public a capitalized cost reduction to the lessee unless the capitalized cost reduction is offered to all potential lessees.
